Contract Idea in One Paragraph
Two parties want to do a deal — for example, a freelance job or a product sale. 
The sender locks GEN in the contract as a deposit. The recipient can activate and later finalize the deal, 
either by taking a payout (funds released to them) or a certificate (logical NFT-like state with metadata). 
If something goes wrong, either side can open a dispute. 
It can be resolved manually by the contract owner or automatically by an AI arbitrator that reads the deal context and returns a structured decision.

