Dispute Resolution
Either party can open a dispute while the deal is INACTIVE or ACTIVE. 
The other side can respond with a counter-argument. After the dispute window closes, the owner resolves it via one of two paths:
Manual — resolve_dispute_owner(deal_id, send_to_recipient, note)
The owner decides who gets the funds and records a note.
AI — resolve_dispute_ai(deal_id)
An LLM arbitrator receives the full deal context (parties, deposit, both sides' reasons, off-chain reference) and returns a structured JSON decision:

json{
  "decision": "sender_refund" | "release_to_recipient",
  "explanation": "..."
}
The explanation is stored on-chain in deal_resolution_note.

